00:01:58.150 --> 00:02:01.519
You may have to solve the
following problem.

00:02:01.519 --> 00:02:04.489
There is some chunk,
maybe a potato,

00:02:04.489 --> 00:02:09.068
and you bring some electric
charge, what does it do?

00:02:09.068 --> 00:02:11.408
That's a meaningful question,
because it does something,

00:02:11.408 --> 00:02:11.750
right?
 

00:02:11.750 --> 00:02:14.669
And nature calculates right
away and does something.

00:02:14.669 --> 00:02:16.128
But if you want to figure out
what happens,

00:02:16.128 --> 00:02:20.834
it's quite complicated,
so a somewhat easier problem is

00:02:20.834 --> 00:02:24.930
the case of the perfectly
conducting potato,

00:02:24.930 --> 00:02:28.830
which is kind of solid metal,
shaped like whatever you like.

00:02:28.830 --> 00:02:32.500
You bring a charge next to it,
what happens?

00:02:32.500 --> 00:02:35.514
That question occurs a lot,
because we do electrical

00:02:35.514 --> 00:02:38.410
experiments in the presence of
many conductors.

00:02:38.410 --> 00:02:41.022
And the simple thing about a
conductor is,

00:02:41.022 --> 00:02:43.508
the whole conductor is one
potential.

00:02:43.508 --> 00:02:48.555
So I want to take a simple
problem and see if we can answer

00:02:48.555 --> 00:02:48.990
it.
 

00:02:48.990 --> 00:02:50.568
Now most problems,
you cannot answer.

00:02:50.568 --> 00:02:52.639
By "cannot answer"
I don't mean in principle.

00:02:52.639 --> 00:02:54.577
In principle,
we know the equations,

00:02:54.577 --> 00:02:57.180
we can solve them,
including the real potato.

00:02:57.180 --> 00:03:00.520
You can actually figure out
everything, but it's too hard.

00:03:00.520 --> 00:03:02.598
You cannot write it in simple
form.

00:03:02.598 --> 00:03:07.331
There are a few simple textbook
examples where you can ask the

00:03:07.331 --> 00:03:09.658
question and you can answer.
 

00:03:09.658 --> 00:03:15.945
And the question you want to
ask is, here is an infinite

00:03:15.945 --> 00:03:20.289
conducting plane and it is
grounded.

00:03:20.289 --> 00:03:21.438
Grounded means what?
 

00:03:21.438 --> 00:03:25.658
You take a wire and you connect
it to the earth.

00:03:25.658 --> 00:03:30.646
Now the point of connecting to
the earth is that the earth is

00:03:30.646 --> 00:03:34.720
pretty close to being an object
at 0 potential.

00:03:34.720 --> 00:03:36.824
In other words,
if you bring a charge from

00:03:36.824 --> 00:03:39.442
infinity to the earth,
the amount of work you do you

00:03:39.442 --> 00:03:40.520
can take to be 0.
 

00:03:40.520 --> 00:03:43.270
And on a daily basis,
people are dumping charge,

00:03:43.270 --> 00:03:46.312
people are taking charge out of
it, but it's so huge,

00:03:46.312 --> 00:03:47.598
it doesn't matter.
 

00:03:47.598 --> 00:03:51.169
It's like one of the reservoirs
you studied in thermodynamics.

00:03:51.169 --> 00:03:53.008
You can take some heat,
you can put some heat.

00:03:53.008 --> 00:03:54.930
It doesn't change its
temperature.

00:03:54.930 --> 00:03:58.663
So the earth is a huge
repository where you can take a

00:03:58.663 --> 00:04:01.270
few charges now and put a few
back.

00:04:01.270 --> 00:04:02.830
It will always remain at 0.
 

00:04:02.830 --> 00:04:06.400
It will force you also to go to
0 potential.

00:04:06.400 --> 00:04:10.961
So that is that plane,
and you have another charge,

00:04:10.961 --> 00:04:15.340
q, you slowly bring
towards that plane.

00:04:15.340 --> 00:04:17.430
You may like to know what's the
answer to this problem.

00:04:17.430 --> 00:04:21.560
What does the field look like
everywhere?

00:04:21.560 --> 00:04:22.908
Now this plane,
for convenience,

00:04:22.908 --> 00:04:24.649
I'm going to be taking to be
infinite.

00:04:24.649 --> 00:04:27.829
If you want a side view of that
plane, it looks like this.

00:04:27.829 --> 00:04:30.122
It divides the whole universe
into two parts,

00:04:30.122 --> 00:04:33.459
where you are with your charge
and the rest on the other side.

00:04:33.459 --> 00:04:36.389
So what will this plane do?
 

00:04:36.389 --> 00:04:39.980
You can see that if it did
nothing, it's in trouble.

00:04:39.980 --> 00:04:42.487
If it did nothing,
this charge at that distance

00:04:42.487 --> 00:04:44.449
will produce a positive
potential.

00:04:44.449 --> 00:04:46.656
At that distance,
it will produce an even bigger

00:04:46.656 --> 00:04:48.629
positive potential,
because it's closer.

00:04:48.629 --> 00:04:51.050
So different parts of the sheet
will be at different potentials.

00:04:51.050 --> 00:04:51.730
That's not allowed.
 

00:04:51.730 --> 00:04:53.060
It's an equipotential.
 

00:04:53.060 --> 00:04:54.120
It's a metal.
 

00:04:54.120 --> 00:04:57.093
It's got to arrange its
potential to be constant,

00:04:57.093 --> 00:05:00.872
and because it's connected to
the ground, that constant has to

00:05:00.872 --> 00:05:01.430
be 0.
 

00:05:01.430 --> 00:05:05.115
So the way it will lower its
potential from your attempts to

00:05:05.115 --> 00:05:08.362
raise it is to suck up some
negative charges from the

00:05:08.362 --> 00:05:09.050
ground.
 

00:05:09.050 --> 00:05:12.625
So negative charge will leave
the ground and somehow come and

00:05:12.625 --> 00:05:15.129
stand in front of this positive
charge,

00:05:15.129 --> 00:05:19.586
maybe something like this,
over some region roughly

00:05:19.586 --> 00:05:24.670
proportional to the distance
between you and the plane.

00:05:24.670 --> 00:05:26.819
Then what will happen is,
the electric field lines,

00:05:26.819 --> 00:05:29.220
which normally go through the
metal if it wasn't there,

00:05:29.220 --> 00:05:33.529
will now of course have to come
and terminate on that metal,

00:05:33.529 --> 00:05:36.886
and they have to terminate
perpendicularly because the

00:05:36.886 --> 00:05:40.560
electric field is always
perpendicular to the conductor.

00:05:40.560 --> 00:05:41.980
You know why, right?
 

00:05:41.980 --> 00:05:44.680
Because if you move along the
conductor, the potential cannot

00:05:44.680 --> 00:05:47.315
change, so the line integral of
E must be 0,

00:05:47.315 --> 00:05:49.815
but basically,
you should not feel any force

00:05:49.815 --> 00:05:51.620
as you move along the plane.
 

00:05:51.620 --> 00:05:53.350
So E is perpendicular.
 

00:05:53.350 --> 00:05:57.370
So some bunch of charges will
be drawn from the ground,

00:05:57.370 --> 00:06:00.720
as necessary,
and this is what will happen.

00:06:00.720 --> 00:06:03.874
The question is,
can you say anything more in

00:06:03.874 --> 00:06:04.519
detail?
 

00:06:04.519 --> 00:06:09.841
Can you actually calculate the
charge distribution on this

00:06:09.841 --> 00:06:11.430
infinite plane?
 

00:06:11.430 --> 00:06:15.185
Can you calculate the force of
attraction between the charge

00:06:15.185 --> 00:06:17.350
you have and the infinite plane?
 

00:06:17.350 --> 00:06:19.771
You know there's going to be
attraction because your charge I

00:06:19.771 --> 00:06:21.750
take to be positive,
and this has got negative.

00:06:21.750 --> 00:06:22.970
They'll attract.
 

00:06:22.970 --> 00:06:24.610
What is the attraction?
 

00:06:24.610 --> 00:06:27.119
These are all well-defined
questions and they exist no

00:06:27.119 --> 00:06:28.540
matter what this is made of.
 

00:06:28.540 --> 00:06:34.149
But for this infinite plane,
we can actually answer it

00:06:34.149 --> 00:06:37.226
So we answer by the following
device, which is what I was

00:06:37.226 --> 00:06:38.930
trying to tell you last time.
 

00:06:38.930 --> 00:06:43.093
If you take that infinite
plane, your conditions are that

00:06:43.093 --> 00:06:47.702
it should be at 0 potential and
to the left of it should be the

00:06:47.702 --> 00:06:50.230
charge q that I put in.
 

00:06:50.230 --> 00:06:52.149
These are the requirements.
 

00:06:52.149 --> 00:06:55.480
So you dream up another problem.
 

00:06:55.480 --> 00:06:59.810
That's a charge -q,
same distance d from

00:06:59.810 --> 00:07:00.709
this one.
 

00:07:00.709 --> 00:07:02.000
Take out the plane.
 

00:07:02.000 --> 00:07:03.550
Forget the plane now.
 

00:07:03.550 --> 00:07:06.211
Think of a new problem,
and -q,

00:07:06.211 --> 00:07:09.089
and you've done that many,
many times.

00:07:09.089 --> 00:07:12.290
The lines go like this.
 

00:07:12.290 --> 00:07:15.009
And you know that on the
perpendicular bisector,

00:07:15.009 --> 00:07:16.803
the lines will be
perpendicular,

00:07:16.803 --> 00:07:18.944
because the potential
everywhere is 0,

00:07:18.944 --> 00:07:19.639
right?
 

00:07:19.639 --> 00:07:22.297
Potential is a scaler and
whatever this guy does,

00:07:22.297 --> 00:07:24.898
that will do - of that,
because it's at the same

00:07:24.898 --> 00:07:26.670
distance, but has -q.
 

00:07:26.670 --> 00:07:30.130
So V is 0,
so E will be

00:07:30.130 --> 00:07:31.670
perpendicular.
 

00:07:31.670 --> 00:07:34.666
Now if you take that
arrangement and look what's

00:07:34.666 --> 00:07:38.238
happening to the left of the
plane, it looks like exactly

00:07:38.238 --> 00:07:40.279
what we want in our problem.
 

00:07:40.279 --> 00:07:43.406
What we demand in our problem
is in this part of the universe

00:07:43.406 --> 00:07:45.762
where I live,
there should be charge

00:07:45.762 --> 00:07:49.709
q, there should be
infinite plane at 0 potential.

00:07:49.709 --> 00:07:52.913
That condition is satisfied by
this field configuration in the

00:07:52.913 --> 00:07:53.860
following sense.
 

00:07:53.860 --> 00:07:58.744
Start with this configuration
and stick in the infinite plane,

00:07:58.744 --> 00:08:03.468
but give it the charge it needs
to terminate all these field

00:08:03.468 --> 00:08:04.269
lines.
 

00:08:04.269 --> 00:08:05.410
How much charge will it need?
 

00:08:05.410 --> 00:08:07.370
You can tell right away.
 

00:08:07.370 --> 00:08:13.759
What's the total charge on this
plane?

00:08:13.759 --> 00:08:17.540
Because all the lines leaving
this have to terminate on this.

00:08:17.540 --> 00:08:21.319
You can see it'll be -q.
 

00:08:21.319 --> 00:08:23.036
It won't be point charge;
it'll be spread out,

00:08:23.036 --> 00:08:24.360
but you need -q on this.
 

00:08:24.360 --> 00:08:28.333
So what we say is,
if you brought the plane in and

00:08:28.333 --> 00:08:31.819
either you give it -q in
advance,

00:08:31.819 --> 00:08:34.845
or you connected it to the
ground, in which case it will

00:08:34.845 --> 00:08:36.330
itself suck up -q.
 

00:08:36.330 --> 00:08:40.515
It'll form this configuration
here, so the infinite plane is

00:08:40.515 --> 00:08:44.561
able to remain where it is
without disturbing the solution

00:08:44.561 --> 00:08:45.908
to the problem.
 

00:08:45.908 --> 00:08:48.792
Therefore the answer to the
original question of what

00:08:48.792 --> 00:08:52.283
happens when you put a q
in front of an infinite plane is

00:08:52.283 --> 00:08:54.889
that as far as you're on the
left of this,

00:08:54.889 --> 00:08:58.303
you can compute anything you
want by taking q and the

00:08:58.303 --> 00:09:01.048
image charge,
-q.

00:09:01.048 --> 00:09:05.784
The field the two of them will
produce will be exactly the

00:09:05.784 --> 00:09:10.769
field this guy and all these
induced charges will produce.

00:09:10.769 --> 00:09:15.364
So this is a way of taking a
solution for a simple problem

00:09:15.364 --> 00:09:19.009
with an equipotential,
sticking a conductor into the

00:09:19.009 --> 00:09:21.548
equipotential,
and giving it the right charge.

00:09:21.548 --> 00:09:27.504
Then the problem of a charge in
front of a conductor is thereby

00:09:27.504 --> 00:09:28.370
solved.
 

00:09:28.370 --> 00:09:31.306
Now there are some mathematical
theorems--I don't have time to

00:09:31.306 --> 00:09:33.279
prove but they're not too hard
in fact.

00:09:33.279 --> 00:09:36.389
I thought of lecturing on that,
but there isn't enough time--

00:09:36.389 --> 00:09:39.743
that show that if you can find
one answer that has the right

00:09:39.743 --> 00:09:42.129
behavior at the boundary of the
region,

00:09:42.129 --> 00:09:43.629
that has got the charges in the
right place,

00:09:43.629 --> 00:09:45.610
is the only answer.
 

00:09:45.610 --> 00:09:46.860
Yes.
 

00:09:46.860 --> 00:09:49.085
Student:  Is the -q
evenly distributed across

00:09:49.085 --> 00:09:49.529
